===Etymology 1===
From {{etyl|enm|en}} {{m|enm|seyen}}, {{m|enm|seien}}, {{m|enm|seggen}}, from {{etyl|ang|en}} {{m|ang|secġan||to say, speak}}, from {{etyl|gem-pro|en}} {{m|gem-pro|*sagjaną||to say}}, from {{etyl|ine-pro|en}} {{m|ine-pro|*sokʷ-h₁-yé-}}, a suffixed ''o''-grade form of {{m|ine-pro|*sekʷ-||to tell, talk}}. Cognate with {{cog|fy|sizze||to say}}, {{cog|nl|zeggen||to say}}, {{cog|de|sagen||to say}}, {{cog|da|sige||to say}}, {{cog|nb|si||to say}}, {{cog|nn|seia||to say}}, {{cog|sv|säga||to say}}.

The adverb and interjection are from the verb.

====Verb====
{{en-verb|says|saying|said}}

# {{lb|en|transitive}} To [[pronounce]].
#: {{ux|en|Please '''say''' your name slowly and clearly.}}
